review_blob: Drank from a bottle. Canadian (Labatt) version, 5.5%, used to be 6.0%. Overall not bad for an ice beer, and leagues ahead of Busch Light. Less watery, with a nice golden colour. Would buy again, but in smaller quantity if possible.

Thought this was OK until I had another beer directly before it. Wow did it taste like cardboard water after that. Unfortunately I had 7 left, but adding lime to this actually makes it drinkable, and enjoyable. Standalone it is terrible.

This beer just appeared at The Beer Store, with no information on Labatts website, or anywhere else on the internet. Seems weird to be launching an Ice beer now, long after the ice bee wars, and under the "Labatt Blue" brand considering AB Inbev has forced Labatt into cutting all marketing for the brand, to focus only on Budweiser and Bud Light. This beer is very drinkable, with little bit of sweetness in its finish, and has a very easy going "mouthfeel" to it. Would buy again.

For 3.5% ABV, I must say this has a lot more flavour than most light beers at 4% and even more so than some between 4-5%. With that said it taste very similar to MooseHead Lager from what I can remember, with that slightly skunky taste. If youre watching your caloric intake, at 90 calories this isnt that bad. Certainly better than Canadian 67 which is 3%, but the extra .5% is worth the 23 calories.

Ahh, so MolsonCoors finally decided to respond to Bud "Light" Platinum. Well BLP is overly sweet and disgusting and.... so is this. Tastes very, very similar. Drank straight from the bottle, all I got was sweetness and pungent alcohol. Bought a four pack, gave three of them away.

I used to despise this brew, but its grown on me slightly. A very light, easily downed beer, with an occasional unpleasant aftertaste, this beer is something great to get drunk on, because of its watery state. The reason it sells so great, is because of its price.

Actually better than I remember it. No aftertaste, not very hoppy, no skuny smell/test. With lime this beer is porbably 50% better. I recommend always drinking this with lime, night and day difference.

Ive had Busch before years ago and didnt like it. Going to a friends house and needing cheap beer, I saw that Busch was on sale at the Beer Store and bought it. So I thought, accidentally grabbed Busch Light. This is BY FAR THE WORST BEER I HAVE EVER CONSUMED. It was skunky, aroma was repulsive, and the after taste was like a kick to the mouth. I am quickly learning that Macro-lights are horrible, but this, this is a step or leap below famous brands such as Bud Light, Blue Light, and even Coors Light. Hell its even worse than Keystone Light.
